### AidFlow API — Distribution / Batches endpoints
# REST Client extension: click 'Send Request' above each block

@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000/api/v1
@token = REPLACE_WITH_JWT_TOKEN

### List batches (501 in Sprint 1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/distribution
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get batch by ID (501 in Sprint 1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/distribution/BATCH_ID
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Create batch (501 in Sprint 1)
POST {{baseUrl}}/distribution
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "programId": "PROGRAM_ID",
  "name": "April 2026 Distribution",
  "scheduledDate": "2026-04-15"
}

### Submit batch for approval (501 in Sprint 1)
POST {{baseUrl}}/distribution/BATCH_ID/submit
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Approve batch (501 in Sprint 1)
POST {{baseUrl}}/distribution/BATCH_ID/approve
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Release batch (501 in Sprint 1)
POST {{baseUrl}}/distribution/BATCH_ID/release
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
